abstract: New York’s onerous voting restrictions have long undercut its reputation as a progressive beacon. Democrats have promised to remake them entirely.

abstract: A former disc jockey, Mr. Leonard brought a sophisticated style to hosting TV sports programs in New York (“Sports Extra”) and on ESPN and CNN.
snippet: A former disc jockey, Mr. Leonard brought a sophisticated style to hosting TV sports programs in New York (“Sports Extra”) and on ESPN and CNN.
lead_paragraph: Lee Leonard, an urbane host of sports and entertainment programs who introduced ESPN to a small audience on the day of its debut in 1979, died on Sunday at his home in South Orange, N.J. He was 89.

headline_main: Michael Flynn, Stocks, Les Moonves: Your Tuesday Briefing

abstract: Delaware’s ambitious bid to offer one-stop shopping for birth control is a social experiment that other states will be watching.
snippet: Delaware’s ambitious bid to offer one-stop shopping for birth control is a social experiment that other states will be watching.
lead_paragraph: When a woman of childbearing age goes to the doctor in most places, she gets standard queries about her smoking, drinking, seatbelt use and allergies. In Delaware, she is now also asked: “Do you want to get pregnant in the next year?”

abstract: The company announced that Mr. Moonves, who was forced out in September after multiple allegations of sexual misconduct, had breached his employment contract.
snippet: The company announced that Mr. Moonves, who was forced out in September after multiple allegations of sexual misconduct, had breached his employment contract.
lead_paragraph: The CBS Corporation, battered by scandal and facing a leadership vacuum, said its former chief executive, Leslie Moonves, misled the company about multiple allegations of sexual misconduct and tried to hide evidence as he made a frenzied attempt to save his legacy and reap a lucrative severance. As a result, the company said Mr. Moonves would not receive his $120 million exit payout.
